{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"G3 container coverage audit (parent WS-EVAL-EXISTING vs this child c156 + full sibling roster): clean — no findings.\n\n4-bucket audit of parent's 5 acceptance criteria:\n- AC1 (3 packaged eval specs, validate_eval_spec-clean, disciplined gates:false cross-family judges, at_least(k)/epochs, coverage threshold, non-empty gold_set): FULLY covered by this child c156 (authors all 3 specs with epochs>=2, at_least(k), coverage threshold, GPT-4o cross-family judge gates:false, non-empty gold_set).\n- AC2 (deterministic-scorer registry; every name -> pure fn; validate_scorer rejects unregistered): STRUCTURAL for c156 (it consumes registered scorers); covered by sibling 476f.\n- AC3 (run_eval() runs live via Inspect; 3 agentic reviewers via context-injection solver + stubbed/fixture repo tools): STRUCTURAL for c156; covered by siblings 4569 (run_eval/Inspect) + 7402 (solver + tool stubbing).\n- AC4 (eval-discipline CI gates all 7 specs at zero API cost; offline tests assert dataset balance + non-empty gold_set): FULLY covered by this child c156 (offline unit tests assert validity/gold_set/balance/registered scorers + eval-discipline CI validates all 7 specs at zero cost); schema/shape-validation half supplied by 476f.\n- AC5 (eval-live workflow_dispatch+weekly, non-blocking, cached, concurrency-capped, fork-safe, spend-cap docs): STRUCTURAL for c156; covered by sibling 4569.\n\nUncovered-criterion sweep against the WHOLE roster: none. Every parent AC is covered by the union of children (AC1->c156, AC2->476f, AC3->4569+7402, AC4->c156/476f, AC5->4569). This child's own ACs map cleanly onto parent AC1+AC4 / Phase 1 scope with no orphan scope."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782579843312772001,"uuid":"39c36bc4-20e9-4a1a-a9c4-ff37f5d9eb8c"}